HEADWORD: Burghmote
<hw>Burgh"mote`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(AS. Law)</fld>
<ety>[<ets>Burgh</ets> + <ets>mote</ets> meeting.]</ety> <def>A court or
meeting of a burgh or borough; a borough court held three times
yearly.</def>⟦br⟧
